{
  "folder": "N6A1Evhl0O3vyf9U",
  "name": "Body is a Canvas",
  "type": "feat",
  "effects": [],
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "gm": "",
      "value": "<p><span lang=\"EN\">You recognize that a body is a vessel that can hold your brand of spellcasting and know how to leverage it, making it a subject to display your talent. You might draw upon it in ways that relate to your medium or motif, in forms such as face paints, tattoos, waxes or words of power. You become Trained in Crafting or Expert if you are already Trained and gain the @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.feats-srd.z0HX5L7bOOrKi0dD]{Tattoo Artist} feat.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"text-decoration:underline\"><span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">Special</span></span><span lang=\"EN\"> If you have the @UUID[Compendium.immortal-ardor.classes.itHebNK68vVzAIBI]{Drawn to Life} feat, you automatically gain the Absorb Familiar Master ability; this does not count towards your number of familiar abilities. If you have the @UUID[Compendium.immortal-ardor.classes.Pl5YLdiMtUCW1XLB]{Catalyst Artist} feat, during daily preparations you can use one of your potential catalysts to instead make a temporary tattoo on your person or one willing ally. The tattoo you make has similar requirements and parameters like your temporary catalysts.</span></p>"
    },
